#Text=Dover ( England )
#Text=Dover is a port in East Kent , in the South East of England .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Dover has been a permanent settlement since at least the time of the Romans , who were the first to record its presence , giving it the name Dubris .
#Text=It also marked the start of Watling Street , a major Roman road .
#Text=The Roman lighthouse built on the present-day site of Dover Castle is one of the oldest buildings in Britain .
#Text=Today Dover is a major port town facing into the English Channel and , at just 21 miles from the French port of Calais , it is the closest port to continental Europe on mainland Britain .
#Text=It is most famous for its white chalk cliffs which have been celebrated in song .
#Text=By car
#Text=The A2 runs north to Canterbury and on to the M2 .
#Text=The A20 follows the coast south to Folkestone , and the A256 heads north towards Ramsgate , Broadstairs and Margate .
#Text=By coach
#Text=National Express operates a regular coach service ( number 007 ) to&from Dover Eastern Docks and Pencester Road , to London Victoria Coach Station .
#Text=It has intermediate stops at Canterbury , some north Kent towns , and local stops in south-east London .
#Text=It 's much cheaper than the train service .
#Text=By train
#Text=The only remaining station is , which is west of the central shopping area , and about a walk from the Eastern Docks .
#Text=Fare and timetable information is available from South East Trains , tel .
#Text=By boat
#Text=Due to its proximity to continental Europe , Dover is one of the busiest cross-Channel ports in the UK , with 18 million passengers passing through its gates every year .
#Text=Regular ferry services operate to Dover from Calais and Dunkirk .
#Text=The ferry between France and Dover costs € 13 - 22 each way if on foot or bicycle , and around £90 for a car , although big discounts are available if booked in advance or with special offers .
#Text=P&O Ferries operate to and from Calais while DFDS Seaways sails from Calais and Dunkirk .
#Text=Other routes are present within the UK ( and might be cheaper ) .
#Text=By bus
#Text=Stagecoach East Kent are the main bus operator in the Dover area .
#Text=Maps , timetables and fare information are available on their website .
#Text=Stagecoach run both urban , rural and inter-urban local buses , including regular buses to Deal , Folkestone , Canterbury and further afield .
#Text=By foot
#Text=Dover is small enough that much of it can reasonably be explored on foot .
#Text=The main shops are in King Street , Cannon Street and Biggin Street .
#Text=See
#Text=Dover Castle , Castle Hill , CT16 1HU , ☏ +441304211067 .
#Text=Known as the " Key to England " , the castle has 2,000 years of history contained within its walls , including a Roman lighthouse , a Saxon church and a Norman keep .
#Text=Below ground a series of casements and tunnels have been dug into the chalk .
#Text=From these tunnels Operation Dynamo ( the Dunkirk evacuation ) was planned . adults £17.00 , children £10.20 , concessions £15.30 .
#Text=Battle of Britain Memorial .
#Text=A very touching memorial dedicated to the men who fought and died in Britain 's most desperate hour .
#Text=Vintage airplanes are also on display .
#Text=Roman Painted House .
#Text=Well-preserved ruins of a Roman townhouse that includes a hypocaust heating system and mosaic fragments .
#Text=The White Cliffs of Dover , Langdon Cliffs , Upper Road , CT16 1HJ , ☏ +441304202756 , ✉ whitecliffs@nationaltrust.org.uk .
#Text=South Foreland Lighthouse , The Front , St Margaret 's Bay , CT15 6HP , ☏ +441304852463 , ✉ southforeland@nationaltrust.org.uk .
#Text=Dover Museum and Bronze Age Boat Gallery .
#Text=Includes a 3,500-year-old wooden boat that was found preserved in mud .
#Text=Grand Shaft .
#Text=Triple staircase constructed in Napoleonic times to enable quick troop movements between Townwall Street and the abandoned Western Heights fortifications .
#Text=Do
#Text=There is a cliff-top 6-km walk from near the Eastern Docks to St Margaret 's Bay .
#Text=Walk the scenic North Downs Way , a walking trail that follows the low hills that run alongside the coast
#Text=Buy
#Text=The main shops are in King Street , Cannon Street and Biggin Street .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Country pubs nearby :
#Text=The New Inn , Canterbury Road , Etchinghill , ☏ +441303862026 .
#Text=A 16th-century coaching inn , country pub and very popular restaurant a short drive from Dover ( junction 12 , M20 ) .
#Text=Fantastic reputation for fine cuisine , open seven days a week for lunches and evening meals .
#Text=Terrific food , real ale , oak beams & cosy atmosphere .
#Text=Indian Cuisine
#Text=Curry Garden Restaurant , 24 High Street , ☏ +441304206357 .
#Text=Daily noon-3PM , 6PM-midnight , including Bank Holidays .
#Text=Dover 's oldest Indian cuisine , on the main high street , close to the town hall .
#Text=A take-away menu is available , offering 10 % discount on all orders over £15 collected from the premises .
#Text=Great special take away offer of 1/2-price take away , every 2nd Sunday of each month , on cash and collect orders only .
#Text=Good selection of dishes on the menu .
#Text=Marine Court Brewers Fayre , Marine court , ☏ +448709906516 .
#Text=On Dover 's seafront with views of Dover .
#Text=Modern pub food .
#Text=Drink

#Text=The Cricketers Pub , Crabble Avenue ( from Dover town centre , go up the one way system to Buckland Brige , turn left at first traffic lights and then first left into Crabble Avenue ; the pub is opposite Dover Rugby and Football grounds ) , ☏ +441304206396 .
#Text=M - W 3PM-midnight , Th - Su noon-1AM .
#Text=The Cricketers is a friendly village pub catering for all ages , in the village of River , opposite the crabble cricket and rugby pitches .
#Text=It is the home of home of Dover Football Club .
#Text=The Cricketers has been an important focal point for the community for over 100 years .
#Text=Cinque Ports Arms , Clarence Place Western Docks CT17 9DQ , ☏ +441304203907 .
#Text=Great Dover pub food : sandwiches , jackets and snacks - all freshly prepared to order .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Ramada Hotel , Singledge Rd , Dover , 4 star , 10 minutes from ferry port
#Text=Number One Guest House , 1 Castle Street .
#Text=Pleasant B&B at the foot of the castle .
#Text=Limited off-street parking available .
#Text=Go next
#Text=St Margaret 's Bay is just a few miles east towards Deal .
#Text=This bay breaks up the white cliffs with a small hillside village , a scenic beach , lots of parking and some eateries ( including the Coastguard Pub , the closest pub to the continent ) .
#Text=On a nice day , the afternoon sun lights up the white cliffs on the French side of the channel quite clearly .
